data.name: Nylon Corporation of America (NYCOA)
data.description:
Nylon Corporation of America, Inc. (NYCOA) is a leading manufacturer of engineered nylon resins. With expertise in custom polymerization, high-efficiency nylon production, and specialty compounding capabilities, NYCOA has developed one of the broadest product portfolios and capability sets in the industry. NYCOA has established itself as a leading supplier of specialty high-performance nylons with over 50 years of experience in specialty production, all based in our manufacturing assets in the USA.


NYCOA's product range includes nylon-6, flexible nylons, high-performance copolymers, long-chain chemistries (including PA 6,12 and PA 6,10 as well as novel long-chain alternatives to PA12 and PA11), impact-resistant nylon, bio-based and recycled-content grades, filled grades, and more. Our specialization in nylon compounding includes impact modified, plasticized, glass fiber/mineral/carbon fiber- reinforced, and flame retardant nylon materials. The ISO 9001:2015 certified company also has the capability to polymerize many unique nylon resins that are in-situ modified with inorganic additives.


NYCOA NYLON PRODUCT FAMILIES

  • Nylon 6 (prime, recycled, filled (glass, carbon, mineral), impact modified, colors,
  • Nylon 6,6 (prime, recycled, filled, with variety of additive packages and color packages)
  • Nylon 6,10
  • Nylon 6,12
  • Long-chain nylon (alternatives to Nylon 11 and Nylon 12)
  • Bio-based nylons
  • Recyclable nylon materials ("clean" polyamide without chemical additives, but with high performance)
  • Recycling solutions (PCR - post-consumer; PIR - post-industrial, aka 'pre-consumer')
  • FDA-certified nylons (food-contact)

data.name: NYCOSIX
data.description: NYCOSIX: decades of experience in excellence and consistency. NYCOSIX grades are available in a wide range of viscosities including low, medium, high, and ultra-high. In addition, nylon extractable levels can be customized, along with certain additive packages to meet customers’ specifications.  Finally, NYCOA’s NYCOSIX grades offer a unique opportunity to incorporate inorganic in-situ, introducing chemistries such as Nano-clay particles and micronized silica particles, as well as key additives that provide performance benefits across different applications.

data.name: NYCOADAPT
data.description: NYCOADAPT : innovation customized to the application. NYCOADAPT products offers a tremendous range of thermal properties, chemical resistances, mechanical properties, crystallinity, viscosity, flexibility, and other performance characteristics that add value to specialized applications in molding, extrusion, film manufacturing and monofilament production, to name a few

data.name: NXTamid-L
data.description: NYCOA's family of specialty engineered specialty copolymer nylons are unique in the performance they offer, and are quite different from shorter chain nylons such as Nylon 6 or Nylon 66. NXTamid-L chemistries were designed as innovative alternatives to Nylon 11 and Nylon 12, and to meet or exceed on the high performance properties such as:flexibilitylower moisture absorptionbroad chemical resistanceIn addition, NXTamid-L have special features that make them unique for high performance applications. NXTamid-L is a fully tunable polymer, meaning NYCOA can customize many properties of our resins:Tunable moisture absorptionAdjustable melt properties and operating temperature rangesCustom compounded grades to incorporate features such as fillers (glass, carbon fiber), UV stabilizers, impact modifiers and moreNXTamid-L is manufactured domestically in the USA, and is available with bio-based components as well.NXTamid products from NYCOA also include NXTamid-T products, such as Nylon 6,12 and Nylon 6,10

data.name: NYCO66
data.description: NYCO66 : Engineering value in PA6.6. Nylon 6.6 represents a unique chemistry with unique properties compared to nylon 6, with a higher melt temperature and differences in thermal properties, abrasion resistance, crystallinity and moisture sensitivity.  NYCOA has used its plastics engineering experience to develop a group of performance engineered nylon 6.6 polymers for our customers, which comprise the NYCO66 family.

data.name: NYCOFILL
data.description: NYCOFILL: Hardness and Rigidity With Added Special PropertiesNYCOA’s NYCOFILL products offer the versatility and resilience of Nylon as an engineered polymer, combined with added performance value from a “FILL” - a homogeneous particle co-extruded with a NYCOA nylon resin. Most commonly, this process is used for the integration of glass fiber fill into nylon.  Glass-filled (or “GF”) nylons exhibit increased structural and impact strength and rigidity, which makes the popular for replacement of a variety of materials, including metal and rubber parts. NYCOFILL grades offer varying amounts of nylon, from 5% - 50%, with varying performance features:Increased tensile strengthIncreased stiffnessAltered thermal expansion and heat deflection temperatureIn addition to GF Nylon, NYCOFILL engineered filled nylons include exotic additives, including carbon fiber and graphene.  Further, we can compound custom NYCOFILL nylon materials to include heat stabilization, lubricant or mold release, color concentrates, and more.

data.name: NYCOTUFF
data.description: Nylon is known and valued for it's toughness - resistance to wear, abrasion, and many chemicals.  However, in some applications there is a need for enhanced impact modification, break resistance, and more.  NYCOTUFF products are custom-made by NYCOA for just such applications.

data.name: NY-FLEX
data.description: NY-FLEX® : Nylon block copolymers with polyetherPolyether -block -amide (PEBA) Copolymers are true elastomeric grades that are based on nylon (Polyamide) hard segment and Polyether soft segment. They deliver excellent recovery and shock-absorbing properties. NYCOA offers PEBA grades in a range of hardness values from 29-80 Shore D. Customized grades are also offered with specialized additive packages for improved thermal stability, hydrolysis resistance, UV resistance, etc.These elastomeric grades are used in sports and leisure, athletic shoes, ski boot components, and technical films. It is also used in furniture manufacturing, masterbatch applications, footwear and tubing

data.heading: Engineering Nylon's Future

data.name: NXTamid-L
data.html_description:
NYCOA's family of specialty engineered specialty copolymer nylons are unique in the performance they offer, and are quite different from shorter chain nylons such as Nylon 6 or Nylon 66.

NXTamid-L chemistries were designed as innovative alternatives to Nylon 11 and Nylon 12, and to meet or exceed on the high performance properties such as:

  • flexibility
  • lower moisture absorption
  • broad chemical resistance


In addition, NXTamid-L have special features that make them unique for high performance applications. NXTamid-L is a fully tunable polymer, meaning NYCOA can customize many properties of our resins:

  • Tunable moisture absorption
  • Adjustable melt properties and operating temperature ranges
  • Custom compounded grades to incorporate features such as fillers (glass, carbon fiber), UV stabilizers, impact modifiers and more


NXTamid-L is manufactured domestically in the USA, and is available with bio-based components as well.


NXTamid products from NYCOA also include NXTamid-T products, such as Nylon 6,12 and Nylon 6,10

data.name: NXTamid L.3
data.description: NYCOA NXTamid-L.3 is a specialty tunable nylon copolymer. It offers high flexibility & chemical resistance alongside low moisture uptake. It also offers improved processability for extrusion or molding applications & better property resistance to low & high temps when compared to similarly flexible polyamides.

data.name: NXTamid L.3 P40
data.description: NYCOA NXTamid-L.3 P40 is a specialty tunable nylon copolymer. It offers extremely high flexibility & chemical resistance alongside low moisture uptake. It also offers improved processability for extrusion or molding applications & better property resistance to low & high temps when compared to similarly flexible polyamides.

data.name: NXTamid L.4
data.description: NYCOA NXTamid-L.4 is a specialty tunable nylon copolymer with properties similar to PA 11 or 12. It offers high flexibility & chemical resistance alongside low moisture uptake. It also offers good processability for extrusion or molding applications & better property resistance to low & high temps when compared to similarly flexible polyamides.

data.name: NXTamid L.5
data.description: NYCOA NXTamid-L.5 is a specialty tunable nylon copolymer. It offers extremely high flexibility with superior chemical resistance alongside low moisture uptake. It also offers improved processability for extrusion or molding applications with better property resistance to low and high temps when compared to similarly flexible polyamides.

data.name: NXTamid L.5 P40
data.description: NYCOA NXTamidLL.5 P40 is a plasticized specialty tunable nylon copolymer. It offers extremely high flexibility & chemical resistance alongside low moisture uptake. It also offers improved processability for extrusion or molding applications & better property resistance to low & high temps when compared to similarly flexible polyamides.

data.name: NXTamid T 2610
data.description: NXTAMID-T 2610 is a Nylon 6,10 that features excellent dimensional stability, with low moisture absorption. This grade is available in custom viscosities, and additive packages. NYCOA offers NXTamid-T 2610 in a range of viscosities (LM, MV, HV for low, medium, and high viscosities, respectively), and with a variety of additive packages for improved performance.

data.name: NXTamid T 2612
data.description: NYCOA NXTamid-T 2612 grades are long-chain nylons that deliver significant performance improvements and a unique balance of properties compared to short-chain materials such as Nylon 6 and Nylon 66. These products offer better dimensional stability, lower moisture absorption, and superior flexibility.

data.name: NXTamid T 2612 STP
data.description: NXTAMID-T 2612 STP is a heat stabilized Nylon 612 grade that offers outstanding toughness, flexibility, and impact strength. It has been specially formulated to give excellent resistance to zinc chloride, automotive fluids and hydrolysis.
